items.title: Please provide some guidance on the difference between v1beta and v1

labels.name: type: question
labels.description: Request for information or clarification. Not an issue.

items.body:
Hi!

I needed to run a AutoML model in batch_predict mode and I tried to find some way to pass input BQ's table and output. But it turned out to be not very clear.
I'd like to share my exprerience and ask for some improvement for documentation.
First of all I looked into BQ's documentation - https://cloud.google.com/vision/automl/docs/predict-batch#automl_batch_predict-python
There's a sample where input and output data are being passed via GCS.
So I went to API doc to look up the reference of batch_predict [method](https://googleapis.dev/python/automl/latest/gapic/v1/api.html#google.cloud.automl_v1.PredictionServiceClient.batch_predict).
And found that there's no an ability to specify any other input and output sources besides gcs. Which looked weird. But then I went to sources on github and found that two versions exist in the repo - v1 and v1beta1.
I wouldn't care but I found `BigQuerySource` and `BigQueryDestination` types in v1beta1. And it was exactly what I needed! 
With REST APIs it's a similar picture: there was BigQuerySource in [v1beta1](https://cloud.google.com/automl/docs/reference/rest/v1beta1/projects.locations.models/batchPredict) and it was removed in v1. 
So we are having two versions of AutoML side-by-side with different APIs and client libs.
Using BigQuery as a source and destination for AutoML is obviously very naturally and handy. It's not quite clear why this ability was removed. 

Obviously v1 is newer than v1beta1. And having a feature in v1beta1 that was removed in v1 provoking using v1beta1 what probably is a bad idea. But it'd be nice to have some guidance for migration and differences description from v1beta1 to v1 then.

items.title: BatchPredict could not start due to empty input CSV file.

labels.name: :rotating_light:
labels.description: This issue needs some love.

labels.name: triage me
labels.description: I really want to be triaged.

items.body:
#### Environment details

1. AutoML Natural Language batch predict (google.cloud.automl_v1.gapic.prediction_service_client.PredictionServiceClient.batch_predict)
2. Ubuntu 16.04
3. 3.7.5
4. 
google-api-core==1.16.0
google-auth==1.11.0
google-cloud-automl==0.10.0
google-cloud-core==1.3.0
google-cloud-storage==1.26.0
google-resumable-media==0.5.0
googleapis-common-protos==1.51.0

#### Steps to reproduce

  1. basically this: https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/python-docs-samples/blob/master/automl/cloud-client/batch_predict.py

#### Code example

```python
logging.info("Make batch prediction")
    
    # Get the full path of the model.
    model_full_id = prediction_client.model_path(
        project, location, model_id
    )
    
    gcs_source = automl.types.GcsSource(input_uris=[input_path])

    input_config = automl.types.BatchPredictInputConfig(gcs_source=gcs_source)
    gcs_destination = automl.types.GcsDestination(output_uri_prefix=output_path)
    output_config = automl.types.BatchPredictOutputConfig(
        gcs_destination=gcs_destination
    )

    response = prediction_client.batch_predict(
        model_full_id, input_config, output_config
    )
    
    params = {"model_id":model_id,
             "model_full_id":model_full_id,
             "gcs_source":gcs_source,
             "input_config":input_config,
             "gcs_destination":gcs_destination,
             "output_config":output_config,
             "input_path":input_path,
             "output_path":output_path}
    
    logging.debug(params)

    logging.debug("Waiting for operation to complete...")
    logging.info("Batch Prediction results saved to Cloud Storage bucket. {}".format(response.result()))
```
Above, `prediction_client` is a `google.cloud.automl_v1.PredictionServiceClient`

#### Stack trace
```
DEBUG:root:Waiting for operation to complete...
DEBUG:google.api_core.retry:Retrying due to , sleeping 0.9s ...
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/home/tc/ml_experiments_plus1/call_segmentation/batch_predict.py", line 113, in <module>
    batch_predict(prediction_client, project_id, compute_region, model_id, input_path, output_path)
  File "/home/tc/ml_experiments_plus1/call_segmentation/batch_predict.py", line 41, in batch_predict
    logging.info("Batch Prediction results saved to Cloud Storage bucket. {}".format(response.result()))
  File "/home/tc/anaconda3_7/envs/ml_experiments_plus1/lib/python3.7/site-packages/google/api_core/future/polling.py", line 127, in result
    raise self._exception
google.api_core.exceptions.GoogleAPICallError: None BatchPredict could not start due to empty input CSV file.
```
The CSV file is not empty, I've tried with a few. The bucket is in us central 1. 


Thanks!

items.title: AutoML: Passing a string to input_uris results in a DeadlineExceeded exception (504)

labels.name: type: question
labels.description: Request for information or clarification. Not an issue.

items.body:
I recognize that passing a string to input_uris may not be its desired usage, but it isn't really clear in the documentation that this needs to be a list of a single string if one isn't referencing multiple files. Raising the DeadlineExceeded exception led me to fiddling with the "timeout" argument in import_data, which resulted in an Unknown exception. This made it difficult to debug.

Seems like raising a ValueError explaining that a list is expected before even sending the request to the API would make much more sense...

#### Environment details

* Microsoft Windows 8.1 Pro 6.3.9600 Build 9600
* Python 3.7.3 in an Anaconda virtual environment
* google-cloud-automl 0.3.0
* google-api-core 1.13.0

  1. Pass a string to input_uris (google.cloud.automl.v1beta1.GcsSource.input_uris) rather than a list of strings, or a list containing a single string.

```python
dataset_full_id = automl_client.dataset_path(project_id, region, dataset_id)
csv_uri = 'gs://{}-lcm/csv/{}.csv'.format(project_id, dataset_name)
input_config = {'gcs_source': {'input_uris': csv_uri}}
response = automl_client.import_data(dataset_full_id, input_config)
```
